# Prompt 028: Advanced Recurrence Patterns (P3)

## Objective
Add support for advanced recurrence patterns like "last Friday of month" and "2nd Tuesday" to handle complex business meeting schedules.

## Context
- **Feature:** Recurring Tasks (P3 - Advanced patterns)
- **Current State:** Daily, weekly, monthly, yearly with intervals and day-of-week selection
- **Gap:** Can't express patterns like "monthly all-hands on first Monday" or "quarterly review on last Friday"
- **Priority:** P3 - Nice-to-have for specific business use cases

## Requirements

### 1. Ordinal Week Patterns
**Purpose:** "First Monday", "Second Tuesday", "Last Friday" of month

**Syntax Examples:**
- "first Monday of month"
- "second Tuesday of month"
- "third Wednesday of month"
- "fourth Thursday of month"
- "last Friday of month"

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/types/index.ts - Extend RecurrenceRule
export interface RecurrenceRule {
  frequency: 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly' | 'yearly';
  interval: number;
  daysOfWeek?: number[]; // Existing
  dayOfMonth?: number; // Existing

  // NEW: For ordinal patterns
  weekOfMonth?: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | -1; // -1 = last
  dayOfWeekInMonth?: number; // 0-6 (combined with weekOfMonth)

  endType: 'never' | 'after' | 'until';
  endCount?: number;
  endDate?: string;
  recurFromCompletion?: boolean;
  templateId?: string;
}
```

### 2. Natural Language Parser Extensions
**Purpose:** Parse ordinal patterns from text

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/utils/naturalLanguageRecurrence.ts
function parseOrdinalMonthlyPattern(input: string): RecurrenceRule | null {
  // "first monday of month" or "first monday"
  const ordinalPattern = /(first|second|third|fourth|last) (monday|tuesday|wednesday|thursday|friday|saturday|sunday)(?: of month)?/i;

  const match = input.match(ordinalPattern);
  if (!match) return null;

  const ordinal = match[1].toLowerCase();
  const dayName = match[2].toLowerCase();

  const weekOfMonth = {
    'first': 1,
    'second': 2,
    'third': 3,
    'fourth': 4,
    'last': -1,
  }[ordinal];

  const dayOfWeek = DAY_NAMES[dayName];

  return {
    frequency: 'monthly',
    interval: 1,
    weekOfMonth,
    dayOfWeekInMonth: dayOfWeek,
    endType: 'never',
  };
}

// "every 2 months on the first monday"
function parseIntervalOrdinalPattern(input: string): RecurrenceRule | null {
  const pattern = /every (\d+) months? on the (first|second|third|fourth|last) (monday|tuesday|wednesday|thursday|friday|saturday|sunday)/i;

  const match = input.match(pattern);
  if (!match) return null;

  const interval = parseInt(match[1], 10);
  const ordinal = match[2].toLowerCase();
  const dayName = match[3].toLowerCase();

  // Same ordinal/day mapping as above
  // ...

  return {
    frequency: 'monthly',
    interval,
    weekOfMonth: /* ... */,
    dayOfWeekInMonth: /* ... */,
    endType: 'never',
  };
}
```

